From: Christian Walter <christian.walter@9elements.com>
Date: Sat, 8 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] dt-bindings: soc: hpe: add GXP I2C passthrough binding

Add YAML binding for the HPE GXP I2C passthrough controller. On HPE
ProLiant Gen11 servers, the GXP ROM holds certain I2C buses during
boot. This driver waits for the ROM to release the buses after host
power-on and then enables I2C passthrough, exposing the passthrough
state as a regulator for downstream drivers (sbtsi, sbrmi, spd5118).

Upstream-Status: Pending
Signed-off-by: Christian Walter <christian.walter@9elements.com>
---
 .../soc/hpe/hpe,gxp-i2c-passthrough.yaml     | 56 ++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 56 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 Documentation/devicetree/bindings/soc/hpe/hpe,gxp-i2c-passthrough.yaml

diff --git a/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/soc/hpe/hpe,gxp-i2c-passthrough.yaml b/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/soc/hpe/hpe,gxp-i2c-passthrough.yaml
new file mode 100644
index 000000000000..a1b2c3d4e5f6
--- /dev/null
+++ b/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/soc/hpe/hpe,gxp-i2c-passthrough.yaml
@@ -0,0 +1,55 @@
+# SPDX-License-Identifier: (GPL-2.0-only OR BSD-2-Clause)
+%YAML 1.2
+---
+$id: http://devicetree.org/schemas/soc/hpe/hpe,gxp-i2c-passthrough.yaml#
+$schema: http://devicetree.org/meta-schemas/core.yaml#
+
+title: HPE GXP I2C Passthrough Controller
+
+maintainers:
+  - Christian Walter <christian.walter@9elements.com>
+
+description: |
+  The HPE GXP SoC ROM holds certain I2C buses during boot. After the
+  host powers on, the ROM eventually releases the buses (indicated by
+  bit 3 of CSM register 0xb0). This driver subscribes to the host
+  power regulator, polls for ROM release, and writes the passthrough
+  enable registers in the CSM block. It exposes the passthrough state
+  as a regulator so downstream I2C client drivers (sbtsi, sbrmi,
+  spd5118) can defer probe until the buses are available.
+
+allOf:
+  - $ref: /schemas/regulator/regulator.yaml#
+
+properties:
+  compatible:
+    const: hpe,gxp-i2c-passthrough
+
+  hpe,csm:
+    $ref: /schemas/types.yaml#/definitions/phandle
+    description:
+      Phandle to the CSM syscon node for register access to ROM state
+      (offset 0xb0) and SPD config (offset 0x110).
+
+  host-power-supply:
+    description:
+      Phandle to the host power regulator. The driver subscribes to
+      regulator events to detect host power-on and power-off.
+
+  regulator-name: true
+
+required:
+  - compatible
+  - hpe,csm
+  - host-power-supply
+
+unevaluatedProperties: false
+
+examples:
+  - |
+    i2c-passthrough {
+      compatible = "hpe,gxp-i2c-passthrough";
+      hpe,csm = <&csm>;
+      host-power-supply = <&host_power>;
+      regulator-name = "i2c-passthrough";
+    };
-- 
